title: PML-N’s Jalal Khan wins PK-79 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Jalal Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-79, Peshawar-VIII by securing 16,031 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Taimoor Saleem Khan who bagged 11,495 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 37.98 per cent.
